<plot>A look at the greatest act of genocide in the 20th Century on four screens. The film, narrated by Joe Mantegna, examines the reasons for the mass slaughter. Among the questions raised are how the most sophisticated nation in the world, Germany, could be reduced to barbarism. Two holocaust survivors tell their stories with a look to a future without racism and hatred.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?243607</url></doc>
